The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 04 December is 116,974 (13,481.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 29 November, there were 5,583 new confirmed cases (643.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 22 November, there were 5,377 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 4% (206 extra cases).
